The paper deals with group testing algorithms, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of linear programming and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the practical applications of group testing in detecting diseases and viruses may also place the paper under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
